Normal Arrays vs. ArrayList

Normal Arrays:

int[] java = new int[100];
int[] arr = new int[n];

Fixed size.

Cannot grow dynamically.

Memory is allocated at declaration.

ArrayList:

ArrayList<Integer> al = new ArrayList<Integer>();



-------------------


import java.util.*;
public class Test{


    public static void main(String args[]){

    //  ArrayList<Integer> al = new ArrayList<Integer>();


    //The ArrayList is created with Integer as its type. is non-primitive datatype

        ArrayList<Integer> l=new ArrayList<Integer>();
        l.add(5);
        l.add(10);
        l.add(15);
        l.add(20);

        System.out.println(l);
    }
}



